
                                                                   byte-size


    FUNCTION
    byte-size  -  get the size from a byte specifier

    USAGE
    byte-size bytespec

    DESCRIPTION
    Returns an integer representing the size component of the byte specifier
    BYTESPEC.  The following identity holds:

    (byte-size (byte s p)) = s

    EXAMPLES
    (byte-size (byte 4 1)) => 4
    (byte-size (byte 6 2)) => 6

    SEE ALSO
    CLtL 12:226, byte, byte-position, deposit-field, dpb, ldb, ldb-test,
    mask-field











































